<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="112" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1446,1617]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,539,1482,1508]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Report associated with sponges:</emphasis>
This species was extracted from &quot;sponge weed&quot; (a symbiosis between the red alga, 
<taxonomicName authority="Zanardini, 1878" authorityName="Zanardini" authorityYear="1878" box="[259,745,1518,1544]" class="Florideophyceae" family="Lomentariaceae" genus="Ceratodictyon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rhodymeniales" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" phylum="Rhodophyta" rank="species" species="spongiosum">
<emphasis box="[259,560,1518,1544]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Ceratodictyon spongiosum</emphasis>
Zanardini, 1878
</taxonomicName>
and the sponge, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Esper" baseAuthorityYear="1794" box="[934,1196,1518,1544]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chalinidae" genus="Haliclona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="cymaeformis">
<emphasis box="[934,1196,1518,1544]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Haliclona cymaeformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), collected at a depth of 
<quantity box="[228,271,1554,1581]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" unit="m" value="1.0">1 m</quantity>
from Great Keppel Island (Great Barrier Reef lagoon, north-eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1040,1145,1554,1581]" name="Australia" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Australia</collectingCountry>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Otto, J. C." box="[1168,1299,1554,1581]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" pagination="279 - 283" refId="ref18454" refString="Otto, J. C. (2000 b) Spongihalacarus longiscutatus n. gen., n. sp., a marine mite (Acari: Prostigmata: Halacaridae) associated with an alga-sponge symbiosis from the Great Barrier Reef Lagoon in Australia. International Journal of Acarology, 26, 279 - 283. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 01647950008684200" type="journal article" year="2000">Otto 2000b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1446,1617]" box="[151,1435,1590,1617]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,260,1590,1616]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Remarks</emphasis>
: A new subfamily, Spongihalacarinae was also established to incorporate this single genus (
<bibRefCitation author="Otto, J. C." box="[1291,1422,1590,1617]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" pagination="279 - 283" refId="ref18454" refString="Otto, J. C. (2000 b) Spongihalacarus longiscutatus n. gen., n. sp., a marine mite (Acari: Prostigmata: Halacaridae) associated with an alga-sponge symbiosis from the Great Barrier Reef Lagoon in Australia. International Journal of Acarology, 26, 279 - 283. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 01647950008684200" type="journal article" year="2000">Otto 2000b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
